There was a similar number of 107 cattle at Powranna on Tuesday with a better run of yearlings and grown steers. The market was fully firm with yearling steers making 226c to 246c, heifers 200c to 226c and leaner 154c to 194c/kg.
Grown steers and bullocks made 210c to 256c/kg.

There was a better quality yarding of 45 cows and the better heavy cows met a stronger market making 170c to 190c, leaner 80c to 120c and very poor 10c to 50c. Heavy bulls made 120c to 150c/kg liveweight.

Market Reporter Richard Bailey
